{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b2-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"355b"},"text":"§ 355b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adverse-event reporting","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b3-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Toll-free number in labeling","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than one year after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-04"},"text":"January 4, 2002","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary of Health and Human Services shall promulgate a final rule requiring that the labeling of each drug for which an application is approved under section 505 of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s355"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 355","children":[],"tail":"] (regardless of the date on which approved) include the toll-free number maintained by the Secretary for the purpose of receiving reports of adverse events regarding drugs and a statement that such number is to be used for reporting purposes only, not to receive medical advice. With respect to the final rule:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b4-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The rule shall provide for the implementation of such labeling requirement in a manner that the Secretary considers to be most likely to reach the broadest consumer audience.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b5-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In promulgating the rule, the Secretary shall seek to minimize the cost of the rule on the pharmacy profession.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b6-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The rule shall take effect not later than 60 days after the date on which the rule is promulgated.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Drugs with pediatric market exclusivity","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id13f6b7b8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"During the one year beginning on the date on which a drug receives a period of market exclusivity under 505A ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002050"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002050"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be preceded by “section”."}],"tail":" of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s355a"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 355a","children":[],"tail":"], any report of an adverse event regarding the drug that the Secretary of Health and Human Services receives shall be referred to the Office of Pediatric Therapeutics established under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s393a"},"text":"section 393a of this title","children":[],"tail":". In considering the report, the Director of such Office shall provide for the review of the report by the Pediatric Advisory Committee, including obtaining any recommendations of such subcommittee "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002051"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002051"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “Committee”."}],"tail":" regarding whether the Secretary should take action under the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] in response to the report."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id13f928b9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s355b/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rule of construction","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Paragraph (1) may not be construed as restricting the authority of the Secretary of Health and Human Services to continue carrying out the activities described in such paragraph regarding a drug after the one-year period described in such paragraph regarding the drug has expired.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id13f928ba-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/109/s17"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–109, § 17","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/1422"},"text":"115 Stat. 1422","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/155/s3/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–155, § 3(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1942"},"text":"117 Stat. 1942","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id13f928bb-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id13f928bc-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id13f928bd-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(1), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch675"},"text":"act June 25, 1938, ch. 675","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1040"},"text":"52 Stat. 1040","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s301"},"text":"section 301 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id13f928be-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Best Pharmaceuticals for Children Act, and not as part of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id13f928bf-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/155"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–155","children":[],"tail":" struck out “Advisory Subcommittee of the Anti-Infective Drugs” before “Advisory Committee”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id13f928c0-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id13f928c1-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2003 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/155"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–155","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2003","children":[],"tail":", except as otherwise provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/155/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 108–155","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s355c"},"text":"section 355c of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
